cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this work, please cite it as below. The German book is
  the authoritative version; an English translation is included.
title: "Horimetrik — Zahlen mit Horizont"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Bürckert"
    given-names: "Christian Felix"
    email: "christian@buerckert.eu"
abstract: >-
  A book and reference implementation on a positional number system
  with decreasing bases: finite factorial horizons, meaning-carrying
  leading zeros, a value/shape duality with two projectors to the
  same identity element, a side fidelity theorem forbidding mixed
  arithmetics, a horizon calculus with exact growth laws, and nine
  integer sequences submitted to the OEIS. Text CC BY 4.0, programs
  MIT. Written with mathematical collaboration by Claude (Anthropic)
  and ideas contributed by GPT (OpenAI).
keywords:
  - mathematics
  - combinatorics
  - number systems
  - mixed radix
  - factorial number system
  - inversion sequences
  - integer sequences
  - OEIS
license: CC-BY-4.0
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.21400755
repository-code: "https://github.com/christianbuerckert/horimetrik"
identifiers:
  - type: doi
    value: 10.5281/zenodo.21400755
    description: "Zenodo archive (books and paper)"
date-released: "2026-07-14"
version: "0.27"
